'''Woo-Woo''' or sometimes just, "Woo" is a derogatory label used by many in the [[Scientific skepticism|skeptic]] community against [[paranormal]], [[occult]], or [[pseudoscientific]] phenomena.  Like an increasing number of formerly pejorative labels, "Woo-Woo" has been more recently reclaimed by some, to use affirmatively.  In this sense, it is usually used in reference to one's ability to conjure [[Magic (paranormal)|"magic"]] or simply one's "mystical power" (as in accessing one's woo-woo).

==Origin==
Although it has been suggested that "Woo Woo" is intended to imitate the eerie background music of [[sci-fi ]]/[[horror films]] and [[TV shows]], the exact origin of this term is not certain.
The term was in use in Eath First in by 1983 on the West coast. It was used to describe both the activities of crystal waving ohming, neopagans and witches who wore their culturally and ecologically missapropropriating spiritualities on their sleeve in preference to and in confusion with political activism, and those who commit  acts of woo. see Miriam Simos aka <p><a href="/wiki/Starhawk" title="Starhawk">Starhawk</a> for an example of woo-woo.

